results.title: I, Magneto...
results.description: The X-Men find Cyclops and Lee at Magneto's ocean base; Cyclops re-joins; Battle royale with Magneto; Kitty performs a Jedi mind trick.

results.title: The Day Kitty Pryde Leaves the X-Men, Is the Day the X-Men Fall!
X-Men Minus One!
results.description: Kitty's parents enroll her in the Massachusetts Academy; White Queen and Storm switch bodies.

results.title: The Hellfire Gambit
results.description: Storm and the White Queen duke it out in each others bodies; X-Men vs. Hellfire Club; Xavier "convinces" Kitty's parents to let her stay at his school.

results.title: And Now For Something Completely Different!
Kitty's Fairy Tale
results.description: Kitty tells Illyana a fairy tale using the X-Men as a character base.

results.title: Reunion
results.description: Corsair comes to Earth seeking the X-Men's help; Corsair is Cyclops' father.

results.title: The Life That Late I Led...
Night Screams!
results.description: Corsair catches up with his sons; Storm becomes a bride of Dracula.

results.title: Chutes and Ladders!
results.description: Illyana loses seven years in Limbo and becomes a teenager with magical powers.

results.title: Beyond the Farthest Star
results.description: Wolvie fights alone against the Brood.

results.title: Rescue Mission
results.description: The X-Men escape the Brood's clutches, but not before they are infected with hatchlings.

results.title: Binary Star!
results.description: The X-Men continue their escape from the Brood but begin to feel the effects of the Brood spawn inside of them; Carol becomes Binary.

results.title: Transfigurations
results.description: Storm fights off her Brood infection.

results.title: Live Free Or Die
results.description: The X-Men all fight off their Brood infections and the Brood Queen is killed.

results.title: The Goldilocks Syndrome (Or: Who's Been Sleeping In My Head?)
results.description: The X-Men return to Earth and battle a Brood infected Xavier; After his recovery, Charlie can walk again; Xavier demotes Kitty to the New Mutants.

results.title: Professor Xavier Is a Jerk!
results.description: Kitty tries to convince Xavier that she should still be with the X-Men (which she does); Lockheed shows up at the mansion and helps Kitty out against a nasty alien; Wolverine leaves for vacation (Next in Wolverine MS #1); Scott arrives in Alaska where he meets Maddie Pryor.

results.title: Catacombs
results.description: The Morlocks kidnap Angel and cut his pin-feathers; Kitty gets a new costume.

results.title: Dancin' In the Dark
results.description: Storm beats Callisto to become leader of the Morlocks; Scott and Maddie begin their romance; Rogue leaves for the X-Men.

results.title: Welcome to the X-Men Rogue...Hope You Survive the Experience!
Rogue
results.description: Rogue comes to the X-Men for help because her powers are out of control; Much to everyone's chagrin, Xavier lets her join.

results.title: Scarlet In Glory
results.description: The X-Men show up in Japan for Wolverine's wedding.

results.title: To Have and Have Not
results.description: Mariko calls off the wedding; Storm adopts her punk look.

results.title: Romances
results.description: Kitty kisses Colossus; Binary joins the Starjammers; Scott and Maddie are engaged.

results.title: Phoenix
results.description: Mastermind makes the X-Men believe that Cyclops and then Maddie are Dark Phoenix; Cyclops and Maddie are married.

results.title: Decisions
results.description: Cyclops leaves for his honeymoon and married life.

results.title: Sanction
results.description: The X-Men run up against Mystique's new Brotherhood of Evil Mutants.

results.title: Hell Hath No Fury
results.description: Mystique uses an attack by the Brotherhood as a diversion so she can sneak into X-Mansion and try to convince Rogue to return to her fold; The Morlocks kidnap Kitty and fake her death.

results.title: What Happened To Kitty?
results.description: Callisto and the Morlocks try to hold Kitty to an old promise to stay with Caliban forever by marrying the two.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #180
results.description: A trip to the Massachusetts Academy turns disastrous for Kitty Pryde and Doug Ramsey.

results.title: Whose Life Is It, Anyway?
results.description: Kitty comes to terms with Storm's punk look; The X-Men leave for Secret Wars.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #181
results.description: With the help of Sunfire, the X-Men battle a terrible beast in Japan. Meanwhile, Senator Kelly proposes the Mutant Control Act in Washington.

results.title: Tokyo Story
results.description: The X-Men return from the Secret Wars and find themselves in Japan where a large dragon is menacing Tokyo (go figure); Wolverine promises to look after a little girl (Amiko) whose parents are killed; Senator Kelly proposes the Mutant Control Act.

results.title: Madness
results.description: Rogue (thinking she is Carol Danvers) rescues one of Ms. Marvel's old flames from SHIELD and tries to re-kindle their relationship; Fury decides to go after Rogue.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #183
results.description: After Colossus breaks up with Kitty, Wolverine takes him into town for a good ol’ talking-to. And that’s precisely when the Juggernaut shows up!

results.title: He'll Never Make Me Cry
results.description: Colossus breaks up with Kitty because of events in Secret Wars and Wolvie and Nightcrawler decide to teach him a lesson by making him go one-on-one against the Juggernaut.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #184
results.description: The mutant energy vampire Selene makes an attempt to capture Rachel Summers, a mutant from the future. The X-Men step in to save her!

results.title: The Past of Future Days
results.description: Forge has created a weapon that takes away super-powers; Selene chases a time tripping Rachel right into the X-Men's arms.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #185
results.description: A meeting between Storm and Rogue goes horribly wrong when Rogue is attacked by Gyrich’s crew, who are packing some major heat—Forge’s neutralizer.

results.title: Public Enemy
results.description: Storm interferes in the government's Rogue hunt and has her powers stripped.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #186
results.description: Now powerless and depressed, Storm is taken in by the mutant Forge, who tries to alleviate her anguish. Meanwhile, Dr. Valerie Cooper is attacked by Dire Wraiths!

results.title: Lifedeath
results.description: "Once upon a time, there was a woman who could fly." Storm comes to grips with the loss of her powers; Dire Wraiths attack.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #187
results.description: Storm, Naze, and Forge are attacked by Dire Wraiths. Can a powerless Storm fight off these alien invaders?

results.title: Wraithkill
results.description: The Dire Wraiths come after Storm and Forge; Naze is killed and the Adversary takes his form.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #188
results.description: To fight the mysterious shadowbeings Magik and Nightcrawler’s main squeeze Amanda Sefton team up for a sorcery-infused battle for the ages!

results.title: Legacy of the Lost
results.description: The X-Men beat back the Dire Wraiths with magical help; The Adversary totally takes over Naze; Lee pulls Magneto out of the ocean; Rachel joins the team and re-caps her history (From Uncanny #141 and 142).

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #189
results.description: Rachel and Magma are on Selene’s tail when the energy vampire heads into the Hellfire Club. What business does the witch have with Sebastian Shaw?

results.title: Two Girls Out To Have Fun
results.description: Storm leaves the team for awhile; Rachel and Magma invade the Hellfire Club to go after Selene, the new Black Queen.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #190
results.description: After the crazed magician Kulan Gath turns Manhattan into a barbarian fantasyland X-Men must stop the ancient wizard from doing permanent harm.

results.title: An Age Undreamed Of
results.description: Kulan Gath (Conan villain) turns Manhattan into a medieval nightmare.

results.title: Raiders of the Lost Temple
results.description: Selene and Kulan are beaten and things stop being so medieval; Nimrod arrives in the present day.

results.title: Fun 'n' Games
results.description: Wolvie and Kitty return from Japan (where they were starring in the Kitty Pryde and Wolverine mini-series); Magus attacks; Xavier is beaten up.

results.title: Warhunt 2
results.description: Kitty Pride (Sprite / Ariel) becomes Shadowcat; Thunderbird comes after the X-Men as revenge for his brother's death (way back in X-Men #95).

results.title: Juggernaut's Back In Town
results.description: Interfering in a battle between Juggernaut and Nimrod, Rogue absorbs all of the X-Men's powers for the first time; Storm is in Africa.

results.title: It Was a Dark and Stormy Night
results.description: Power Pack's parents forget who they are and the kids end up in the Morlock tunnels with a new family; The X-Men intervene.

results.title: What Was That?!
results.description: A group of campus mutie haters take on the X-Men; The X-Men try to adjust to having Magneto around; Kitty smokes one of Wolvie's cigars.
